wikipedia_page.main: Henry George "Harry" Blacklidge (14 July 1884 – 23 May 1917) was an English cricketer. He played seven first-class matches for Surrey between 1908 and 1913.In 1914, Derbyshire signed him up as a coach with the intention to play him when he qualified. In the First World War, Blacklidge was a staff sergeant on the army gymnastic staff. He died from dysentery while serving in Amarah, Mesopotamia.
